From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Use --inplace flag for Cabal register to ensure correct package database

When using a different bootstrap GHC version (e.g., 9.6.7 to build 9.2.8),
packages need to be registered in the correct Stage0 package database.

The Cabal 'register' command does NOT support --package-db=PATH - it only
has --user/--global choice options. The package database path is determined
from LocalBuildInfo set during configure.

The --inplace flag tells Cabal to register the package in the build location
using the package database from the configure step, rather than trying to
register to user/global databases.

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs b/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs
--- a/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Hadrian/Haskell/Cabal/Parse.hs
@@ -191,4 +191,5 @@ registerPackage context@Context {..} = do
     let v = if verbosity >= Loud then "-v3" else "-v0"
     traced "cabal-register" $
         C.defaultMainWithHooksNoReadArgs C.autoconfUserHooks gpd
-            [ "register", "--builddir", ctxPath, v ]
+            [ "register", "--builddir", ctxPath, "--inplace", v ]
+
 -- | What type of file is Main
